==Chinese==

===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|聿|日|t1=|t2=sun|ls=ic}}. Used to mean “daytime” in ancient texts.

The significance and meaning of the {{zh-l|*聿}} component, as present in the {{w|oracle bone inscriptions}}, is not clear. Various theories exist, including that it serves as a phonetic component, in which case the character would be a {{Han compound|聿|日|c1=p|c2=s|t2=sun|ls=psc|nocap=y}}.

===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|s=昼|alt=𦘘,𦘙,𣅯}}
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*g-duk||daytime; noon}} (STEDT). Cognate with {{cog|bo|གདུགས||midday; umbrella}}.

